Package: mypkgr
Title: Example Of A Package For Teaching HeavyR
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(person("Boris", "Hejblum", email = "boris.hejblum@u-bordeaux.fr", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Robin", "Genuer", email = "robin.genuer@u-bordeaux.fr", role = c("aut"))
           )
Description: A collection of function for computing the density for a 
             multivariate Gaussian distibution. Several implementations are 
             provided to examplify the different techniques for optimizing and 
             accelerating R codes.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.2)
Imports: future, 
         future.apply, 
         itertools, 
         Rcpp,
         pbapply
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Suggests: testthat, mvtnorm, covr, microbenchmark
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo
URL: https://github.com/borishejblum/mypkgr, https://borishejblum.github.io/mypkgr/
BugReports: https://github.com/borishejblum/mypkgr/issues
NeedsCompilation: yes
